## Discoveries worth keeping
- **Under FORCE RLS, Postgres hides which UNIQUE constraint failed.** Prisma surfaces `target: null` and "(not available)" — by design, to prevent cross-tenant info leak. Worked around with a SECURITY DEFINER pre-check function (`auth_check_signup_uniqueness`) that returns only booleans. Saved as memory: feedback-rls-hides-constraint-name.
- **Vitest's default esbuild transform doesn't emit decorator metadata.** NestJS DI silently returns undefined for injected fields in any spec that spins up a real test module. Fixed by adding `unplugin-swc` + `@swc/core` to apps/api and configuring vitest.config.ts. Saved as memory: feedback-vitest-decorator-metadata.

## Decisions
- Approved approach B (argon2 directly, manage Session ourselves) over full Better Auth integration for Prompt 3 — proportional to scope, deferred properly via ADR-001
- Audit log for signup is written inline inside the same transaction, not via the BullMQ queue. Comment in auth.service.ts explains why (no school_id exists yet when a queue worker would dequeue → loses atomicity)
- Pre-check uniqueness rather than translate post-hoc — single extra roundtrip on signup is fine; signup is rare

